The paper deals with the problem of embedding covert messages in a broadcast channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of innocent codebooks and the analysis of the channel parameters suggest a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The consideration of an adversary and the need for secrecy also suggest a possible connection to security and privacy (cs.SI).
